The paper deals with structured prediction, which is a common problem in machine learning. The focus is on logical constraints among variables inferred by different classifiers, which suggests that the paper is likely to be in the areas of machine learning, artificial intelligence, and natural language processing. The paper proposes several methods and provides theoretical results, which suggests that it is likely to be in the areas of machine learning and theoretical computer science. The experiments are conducted on ten different datasets, which suggests that the paper is likely to be in the areas of machine learning and data science. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
